    {
      "text": "A patient undergoing treatment for eclampsia at present. When should the subsequent administration of MgSO4 be skipped?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Absence of knee jerk reflex"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Urine output of more than 45 mL/hr"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Respiratory rate of more than 14/min"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "None of the above"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A) Absence of knee <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b88c1802e21692777190700ee5b998\">jerk</span> reflex</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>In <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a40b72bf2d1692777186cdae9f4e42\">eclampsia</span> management, the <strong>absence of deep <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"606c2acae5169277720052151cb04c\">tendon</span> reflexes (such as knee jerks) </strong>can be a sign of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">magnesium</span> toxicity.</li>\n\t<li>Magnesium <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"535af9a2181692777199309af44d24\">sulfate</span> (MgSO4) is administered to prevent seizures, but an excessive <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b5bd69c9791692777186a40f45ffb6\">dosage</span> can lead to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">magnesium</span> toxicity, which depresses the central nervous system, causing loss of deep <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"606c2acae5169277720052151cb04c\">tendon</span> reflexes.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Magnesium <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"535af9a2181692777199309af44d24\">Sulfate</span> Toxicity</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Monitor <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">magnesium</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"535af9a2181692777199309af44d24\">sulfate</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d3323d4b271692777200122ea879e5\">toxicity</span> by observing deep <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"606c2acae5169277720052151cb04c\">tendon</span> reflexes, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">respiratory</span> status, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0096f2a7631692777201eb9f21d5a7\">urine</span> output (primarily excreted by kidneys)</li>\n\t<li>Impaired <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4aa6035df41692777190b41d4a1583\">kidney</span> function can lead to toxicity.</li>\n\t<li>Loss of patellar/ knee reflexes at ~12 mg/dL is an early warning sign.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>MgSO₄ Monitoring (Before Each Maintenance Dose):</strong></p>\n\n<p>Avoid the next dose if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Patellar <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"20f478f55f1692777197e351415f8f\">reflex</span> is absent.</li>\n\t<li>Urine output <30 mL/hour in the last 4 hours.</li>\n\t<li>Respiratory rate <16 breaths/min.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Serum <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">Magnesium</span> Testing:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Routine testing is not recommended.</li>\n\t<li>Test 4-6 hours after starting <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3562d699c516927771909a426ea8ef\">infusion</span> to adjust rate (target: 4-7 mEq/L or 4.8-8.4 mg/dL).</li>\n\t<li>Elevated <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ffaec13de169277719828374cfda0\">serum</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2ead0fd0301692777185187bd72768\">creatinine</span> (≥1.0 mg/dL) to assess <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4aa6035df41692777190b41d4a1583\">kidney</span> function.</li>\n\t<li>Check for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d3323d4b271692777200122ea879e5\">toxicity</span> signs (diminished reflexes, breathing issues) to confirm diagnosis and guide treatment. Administer fluids cautiously to avoid <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9d02a99d051692777194aa3375023b\">overload</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10e2dee19e1692777196673db90c23\">pulmonary</span> edema.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Adverse Effects of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">Magnesium</span> Sulfate</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Mechanism:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Acts as a smooth muscle relaxant.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Serum <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">Magnesium</span> Level</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Effect</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>5–9 mg/dL</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p>Therapeutic range</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>9 mg/dL</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p>Loss of knee <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b88c1802e21692777190700ee5b998\">jerk</span> reflex</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>12 mg/dL</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p>Respiratory depression occurs at ~12 mEq/L (14.4 mg/dL) due to muscle paralysis</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>30 mg/dL</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:middle\">\n\t\t\t<p>Cardiac arrest</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Management of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">Magnesium</span> Toxicity:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Immediate Actions:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Administer 10 mL 10% <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"54de8b79a91692777183e608bc0dd4\">calcium</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ff3235f97616927771884121a800e7\">gluconate</span> IV over 3 minutes to reverse mild to moderate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">respiratory</span> depression.</li>\n\t<li>Discontinue <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">magnesium</span> sulfate.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Further Steps:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Administer <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b1527c07251692777203d317fb2eb0\">furosemide</span> to increase <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0b72f5e96b16927772018dec8a87e2\">urinary</span> excretion.</li>\n\t<li>Severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">respiratory</span> depression requires <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"83e66fab2f1692777190a43a6e300f\">intubation</span> and mechanical ventilation.</li>\n\t<li>The effects of IV <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"54de8b79a91692777183e608bc0dd4\">calcium</span> may be short-lived if steady-state <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d3323d4b271692777200122ea879e5\">toxicity</span> is present.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Urine output more than 45 mL/hr (Option B)</strong> suggests adequate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b9356afdba16927771979d068c6587\">renal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"33dfead74b1692777195931780bd9e\">perfusion</span> and function. This is a positive sign, indicating that the kidneys are adequately eliminating <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">magnesium</span> and other waste products.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Respiratory rate more than 14/min (Option C): </strong>While an elevated <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">respiratory</span> rate can indicate potential issues, it is not a specific <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9f524cc9601692777194d19de23a85\">parameter</span> for withholding MgSO4. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">Respiratory</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"afafb9026e1692777186e3dd168fa8\">distress</span> could be caused by various factors, and further evaluation is necessary to determine the underlying cause.</p>\n\n<p> </p>",
