    {
      "text": "All of the following are clinical uses of Magnesium Sulphate (MgSO₄), except:",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Decreases the incidence of placental abruption"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Reduces the incidence of seizures in preeclampsia"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Neuroprotective"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Improves renal blood flow"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A) Decreases the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"17cd3771bb1692777190950c142dbe\">incidence</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"797686400a16927771956b27d401ff\">placental</span> abruption </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Magnesium Sulfate (MgSO₄)</strong> does not reduce the risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"797686400a16927771956b27d401ff\">placental</span> abruption.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:701px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Aspect</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Details</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>MOA</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>NMDA Receptor Blockade</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Calcium Channel Blockade: reduces <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"54de8b79a91692777183e608bc0dd4\">calcium</span> influx into neurons.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Vasodilation: Improves cerebral <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"82cc227a1c169277718387905b50c6\">blood flow</span> and reduces cerebral edema, dilates <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59ff8b38191692777201150e72ebc3\">uterine</span> arteries, increases endothelial <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"09cefe16671692777196efd2064187\">prostacyclin</span> production and inhibits <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e7032bae7f1692777195d693722e54\">platelet</span> activation. <strong>(Option D ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Uses</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Prevent seizures in severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1fa06d396c1692777196050a5db718\">preeclampsia</span> and eclampsia. Prevent <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c64e3a661b1692777197afc2ff7bca\">recurrent</span> seizures in eclampsia. <strong>(Option B ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Tocolytic effect (delaying <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ac9f7287191692777196e8c02d1f3d\">preterm</span> labor)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Neuroprotective -Protects the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ac9f7287191692777196e8c02d1f3d\">preterm</span> baby's brain from damage by reducing the risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bf99099c3816927771846b1f20893d\">cerebral palsy</span> <strong>(Option C ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Therapeutic Range</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><strong>To control fits the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9627da6bc21692777194438ac75f8d\">optimum</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ffaec13de169277719828374cfda0\">serum</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4d7ed0baae169277719199f6e9ab7b\">magnesium</span> is 4.8–8.4 mg/dL (4–7 mEq/L). Deep <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"606c2acae5169277720052151cb04c\">tendon</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"20f478f55f1692777197e351415f8f\">reflex</span> loss at 9 mg/dL (>7 mEq/L).</strong></li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>C/I</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Myasthenia gravis, hypocalcemia, moderate-to-severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b9356afdba16927771979d068c6587\">renal</span> failure, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e1fb96fd2416927771830dfed40e14\">cardiac</span> ischemia, heart block, myocarditis.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Avoid if alternatives are justified.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Administration and Dosage</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Administer: Intravenously or intramuscularly.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Loading dose: 4–6 g IV over 20–30 minutes. (Zuspan or Sibai regimen)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Maintenance: 1–2 g/hour IV. Monitor <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0096f2a7631692777201eb9f21d5a7\">urine</span> output and reflexes.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Dosage Adjustment</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Adjust for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b9356afdba16927771979d068c6587\">renal</span> dysfunction.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Adverse Effects</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Primarily smooth muscle relaxant: Respiratory depression (at 12 mg/dL) and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e1fb96fd2416927771830dfed40e14\">cardiac</span> arrest (at 30 mg/dL).</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Manage with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"54de8b79a91692777183e608bc0dd4\">calcium</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ff3235f97616927771884121a800e7\">gluconate</span> 10% and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b1527c07251692777203d317fb2eb0\">furosemide</span> if needed.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>",
