      "text": "A 28-year-old primigravida woman with a history of preeclampsia undergoes a cesarean section at term. Her BMI is 37. She is currently stable in the postnatal ward.Which of the following is the most appropriate prophylaxis to prevent DVT for this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Warfarin"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Clopidogrel"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Aspirin"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "LMWH"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: D) </strong>LMWH</p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation: </strong>The correct answer is <strong>low <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b2df2436bf1692777193d90e9c0132\">molecular weight</span> heparin</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>This patient has <strong>multiple <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d885759d516927771966b84bfa470\">postpartum</span> VTE risk factors</strong>:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Cesarean delivery (surgical risk)</li>\n\t<li>Obesity (BMI ≥30)</li>\n\t<li>Hypertensive disorder of pregnancy (preeclampsia)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>According to <strong>RCOG</strong>, women with ≥2 persisting risk factors should receive <strong>LMWH <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bc36e9b9381692777196b5f9a2f79c\">prophylaxis</span> for at least 10 days postpartum</strong>. LMWH is preferred because it</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Has proven <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7f80be61231692777187391e91e867\">efficacy</span> in preventing DVT and PE in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d885759d516927771966b84bfa470\">postpartum</span> women</li>\n\t<li>Does not cross into breast milk</li>\n\t<li>Has predictable <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a8683fba3b1692777195731bac4131\">pharmacokinetics</span> and easy once-daily dosing for prophylaxis</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Warfarin</strong> <strong>(Option A):</strong> While safe in breastfeeding, it is not used for <em>initial</em> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d885759d516927771966b84bfa470\">postpartum</span> VTE <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bc36e9b9381692777196b5f9a2f79c\">prophylaxis</span> unless there’s another indication (e.g., <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9f49b9e654169277719222150eda60\">mechanical heart</span> valve).</p>\n\n<p><strong>Clopidogrel</strong> <strong>(Option B):</strong> Antiplatelet agent used for arterial <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3e745919391692777200fae21b7251\">thrombosis</span> prevention, not <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"96e7e3fecc16927772018cb9f8c8cd\">venous</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3e745919391692777200fae21b7251\">thrombosis</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bc36e9b9381692777196b5f9a2f79c\">prophylaxis</span> in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d885759d516927771966b84bfa470\">postpartum</span> women.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Aspirin</strong> <strong>(Option C):</strong> Used during pregnancy to reduce <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1fa06d396c1692777196050a5db718\">preeclampsia</span> risk; not effective for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d885759d516927771966b84bfa470\">postpartum</span> DVT prevention.</p>",
